Client of Kourend/Quick guide:
{{Quick guide}}
{{Infobox Quest
|name = Client of Kourend
|number = 130
|image = [[File:Client of Kourend.png|300px]]
|members = Yes
|release = [[20 April]] [[2017]]
|update = Client of Kourend
|series = [[Great Kourend quest series|Great Kourend]]
|difficulty = Novice
|developer = Mod Wolf
}}
==Details==
{{Quest details
|start = Speak to [[Veos]] at [[Port Piscarilius]].
|difficulty = Novice
|description = Will you help Veos handle a mysterious client?
|length = Medium
|items = *[[Feather]] ([[Stripy feather|Stripy]] and coloured feathers work too.)
'''Recommended:'''
*[[Amulet of Glory]] to travel to [[Draynor Village]] to start quest, or [[Falador Teleport]].
*[[Games necklace]] OR access to [[Fairy rings]] and have the [[Kourend]] fairy ring activated by talking to [[Trossa]] with 80,000 [[Coins]] OR using the [[Lovakengj Minecart Network]].
*[[Weight-reducing clothing]] such as [[Graceful outfit]]
*[[Stamina potion]]s (will make the quest drastically shorter)
*[[Ring of charos]] (a) for extra dialogue at the end of the quest
*6 casts of [[Kourend Castle Teleport]] (69 {{Skill clickpic|Magic}} required) to shorten the running distance between the majority of House's [[General Store]]s and to get to [[Veos]]
|kills = None
}}

==Walkthrough==
===Getting started===
{{Checklist|
*Travel to [[Port Piscarilius]] by talking to [[Veos]] at the northernmost dock of [[Port Sarim]] just south of the pub. (Use [[amulet of glory]] to travel to [[Draynor Village]] then run around the wall to the west of the village to the docks)
*Once there, talk to [[Veos]] again to start.{{Chat option|3 Have you got any quests for me?|1 Sounds interesting! How can I help?}}
*He will give you an [[enchanted scroll]].
*Use your feather on the enchanted scroll to get an [[enchanted quill]].
}}

===Speaking to the store owners===
*Visit the following districts and speak to their respective store owners about their House and gaining favour:
<gallery>
Leenz location.png|[[Leenz]] from [[Port Piscarilius]]<br>{{Chat option|3 Can I ask you about the Piscarilius house?|3 Why should I gain favour in Piscarilius?}}
Horace location.png|[[Horace]] from [[Hosidius]]<br>{{Chat option|4 Can I ask you about the Hosidius house?|3 Why should I gain favour in Hosidius?}}
Quartermaster Briget location.png|[[Jennifer (Shayzien)|Jennifer]] from [[Shayzien]]<br>{{Chat option|3 Can I ask you about the Shayzien house?|3 Why should I gain favour in Shayzien?}}
Munty location.png|[[Munty]] from [[Lovakengj]]<br>{{Chat option|4 Can I ask you about the Lovakengj house?|3 Why should I gain favour in Lovakengj?}}
Regath location.png|[[Regath]] from [[Arceuus]]<br>{{Chat option|4 Can I ask you about the Arceuus house?|3 Why should I gain favour in Arceuus?}}
</gallery>
{{Checklist|
*Return to [[Veos]] after speaking with all store owners. {{Chat option|4 Let's talk about your client...}}
*Use your [[Games necklace]] [[Wintertodt Camp]] teleport and run south until you reach the dark terrain then west or head to a [[Fairy rings|Fairy Ring]] to go to the [[Dark Altar]] ([[fairy ring]] code {{Fairycode|CIS}}).
*Activate the [[Mysterious orb (Client of Kourend)|mysterious orb]] near the Dark Altar.
*Use a [[Kourend Castle Teleport]] and head back to [[Veos]] {{Chat option|3 Let's talk about your client...}}.
}}

Quest complete!

==Rewards==
{{Quest rewards
|name = Client of Kourend
|image = [[File:Client of Kourend reward scroll.png|centre]]
|qp = 1
|rewards =
*Two [[Antique lamp (Client of Kourend)|antique lamps]] which provide 500 XP each in a skill of the player's choosing.
*[[Kourend favour certificate]]. Reading it grants 20% favour in a House of your choosing.
*[[Kharedst's memoirs]]
}}
{{Client of Kourend}}

Demon Slayer/Quick guide:
{{external|rs}}
{{QG}}
{{Infobox Quest
|name = Demon Slayer
|image = [[File:Demon Slayer.png|300px]]
|number = 2
|members = No
|release = [[4 January]] [[2001]]
|update = Runescape beta is now online!
|series = None
|difficulty = Novice
|developer = Paul Gower
}}
==Details==
{{Quest details
|description=A mighty demon is being summoned to destroy the city of [[Varrock]]. You find out you are the one destined to stop him (or at least try).
|start=Speak to the [[Gypsy Aris|Gypsy]] in the tent on the western side of [[Varrock Square]].
|difficulty=1
|length=Medium
|members=No
|requirements=Capable of defeating a level-27 [[demon]] aided by three level-20 [[Dark Wizard (20)|Dark wizards]] and two level-7 Dark wizards.
|items=*1 [[coins|coin]]
*A [[bucket of water]] (can be obtained during quest)
*25 [[bones]] (can't be [[noted]], but can be delivered a few at a time)
|recommended='''Recommended:'''
*Some [[food]] and [[armour]]
*A means of [[teleportation]] or transportation to get to [[Varrock]] and the [[Wizards' Tower]] south of [[Draynor Village]] and west of [[Lumbridge]]
|kills = [[Delrith]] ''(level 27)''
}}
==Walkthrough==
{{Checklist|
*Speak with the [[Gypsy]] in her tent in [[Varrock Square]] and give her 1 gp. {{Chat option|1Ok, here you go.|2Okay, where is he? I'll kill him for you!|3So how did Wally kill Delrith?|4Where can I find Silverlight?}}
**'''Remember the incantation [[Wally]] chants in the cutscene as it varies from player to player.'''
*Speak to [[Sir Prysin]] on the ground floor at the south-west corner of [[Varrock palace]] {{Chat option|3Gypsy Aris said I should come and talk to you.|1I need to find Silverlight.|2He's back and unfortunately I've got to deal with him.|2And why is this a problem?}}
}}

===First key===
{{Checklist|
*Go to north-west corner of the palace and go up two flights of stairs.
*Speak to [[Captain Rovin]] about the demon. {{Chat option|3Yes I know, but this is important.|1There's a demon who wants to invade this city.|2Yes, very.|2It's not them who are going to fight the demon, it's me.|3Sir Prysin said you would give me the key.|1Why did he give you one of the keys then?}}
}}

===Second key===
{{Checklist|
*Go to the ground floor north-east room that looks like a kitchen.
*Use the bucket of water on the drain outside of the eastern kitchen wall. (If you need a bucket, there is one directly upstairs from the kitchen.)
*Climb down the manhole east of the palace.
*Take the west path down to the end and take the rusty key from the floor. (It does not appear on the minimap)
}}

===Third key===
{{Checklist|
*Take 25 un-noted bones from your bank.
**[[File:Ultimate ironman chat badge.png]] Ultimate Ironmen: You can deliver the bones a few at a time. You do not have to deliver all 25 at once.
*Go to [[Wizards' Tower]] (south of [[Draynor Village]]) ([[fairy ring]] code {{fairycode|DIS}}).
*Climb up stairs and talk to [[Wizard Traiborn]]. {{Chat option|3I need to get a key given to you by Sir Prysin.|3Well, have you got any keys knocking around?|2I'll get the bones for you.}}
*He will ask for 25 [[bones]] (noted will not work); bring him these and he will give you his key.
}}

===Delrith===
{{Checklist|
*Return to Sir Prysin and give him the keys.
*Wield Silverlight and go to the [[Dark wizard]]s by Varrock's south entrance. A cutscene will occur.
*Defeat [[Delrith]]; right-click Delrith and banish him with the incantation seen earlier. The incantation varies from player to player; the gypsy will remind players of the incantation if forgotten.
*Quick chat reference:
**Carlem {{Chat option|1}}
**Aber {{Chat option|2}}
**Camerinthium {{Chat option|3}}
**Purchai {{Chat option|4}}
**Gabindo {{Chat option|5}}
}}

'''Quest complete!'''

{{Demon Slayer}}

Enter the Abyss/Quick guide:
{{Quick Guide}}
{{Quest details
|start = The [[Mage of Zamorak]] at the end of the [[River Lum]] in the [[Wilderness]] (Roams levels 4-7).
|description = In the Abyss miniquest, the player helps the [[Zamorak]]ians access the [[rune essence mine]]s so that they can craft their own runes. Previously, it had been a [[Saradomin]]ist secret, but the [[Mage of Zamorak]] asks for the player's help in learning it.
|length = Short, long without teleports
|requirements = *Completion of [[Rune Mysteries]]
|items = None
'''Recommended:'''
*[[Varrock]] and [[Ardougne]] teleport runes and a method of teleportation to [[Edgeville]] (e.g. [[Amulet of glory]]) would be helpful.
