==Details==
{{Quest details
|start = Go to [[Shilo Village (location)|Shilo Village]] and talk to [[Yanni Salika]].
|difficulty = 3
|description = If you're fresh to [[Shilo Village (location)|Shilo Village]] after solving the mystery (or even if you did it some time ago), you may like to check out Yanni Salika's antiques shop.

He's a busy chap revamping antique items, checking out new stock from potential adventurers and maybe he'll have a small<sup>1</sup> favour to ask of you? Probably nothing particularly large, Yanni isn't a demanding<sup>2</sup> person, should hardly take you any time<sup>3</sup> at all really, something to do when you have a spare moment.

That's assuming there aren't any complications.

1: - Perception of the word "small" may be open to interpretation.

2: - In a recent vote, Yanni Salika was only voted the second most demanding person in Shilo Village.

3: - As everyone knows, time is relative.
|length = Very Long (1 Hour)
|requirements = *{{Skill clickpic|Agility|36}} [[Agility]] can be boosted
*{{Skill clickpic|Crafting|25}} [[Crafting]]
*{{Skill clickpic|Herblore|18}} [[Herblore]]
*{{Skill clickpic|Smithing|30}} [[Smithing]]
*Completion of the following quests:
**[[Rune Mysteries]]
**[[Shilo Village]]
|items = *4 [[steel bar]]s
*A [[bronze bar]]
*An [[iron bar]]
*A [[chisel]]
*~4,000 [[coins]]
*2 [[guam leaf|guam leaves]]
*A [[marrentill]]
*A [[harralander]]
*A [[hammer]]
*An [[empty cup]] (can be obtained during the quest)
*5 [[pigeon cage]]s (can be obtained during the quest)
*:'''Note:''' you do not need to let the pigeons out of the cage in order for these to be used for the quest
*A [[pot]] (Can be obtained during the quest. However, it is faster to already have one.)
*A [[bowl of hot water]] (Can be obtained during the quest. However, it is faster to already have one.)
'''Recommended:'''
*[[Weight-reducing clothing]] (for every step of the quest except the [[Slagilith]] part)
*Several teleports
*[[Energy potion]]s
*[[Stamina potion]]s
*Two of each cut [[opal]], [[Jade (gem)|jade]], [[sapphire]] and [[red topaz]] gems (can be mined with 40 [[Mining]])
*The best [[pickaxe]] you can wield
*A [[Dramen staff|Dramen]] or [[Lunar staff]]
*Some [[armour]] and [[food]] (only for the boss battle)
|kills = *[[Slagilith]] ''(level 92)''
*[[Dwarf gang member]]s ''(level 44/48/49)'' ([[multicombat area]])
}}
==Walkthrough==
''NOTE: Many NPCs are involved in other quests and activities. Some chat options provided below may be inaccurate depending on your state in those quests and activities.''

===Agreeing to the favours===
{{Checklist|
*Talk to [[Yanni Salika]] in Shilo Village (north of the bridge at the quest icon). {{Chat option|2Is there anything else interesting to do around here?|5Ok, see you in a tick!|1Il'l get going then!}}
*Talk to a [[Jungle forester]] south of Shilo at the tree line. {{Chat option|1I need to talk to you about red mahogany.|1Ok, I'll take your axe to get it sharpened.}}
*Talk to [[Brian]] in the [[Port Sarim]] axe shop. {{Chat option|3Do you sharpen axes?|2Look, can you sharpen this cursed axe or what?|4Ok, ok, I'll do it! I'll go and see Aggie.}}
*Talk to [[Aggie]] in [[Draynor Village]]. {{Chat option|2Can I ask you about being a character witness?|3Let me guess, you're going to ask me to do you a favour?|2Oh, Ok, I'll see if I can find Jimmy.}}
*Talk to [[Johanhus Ulsbrecht]] near the prison inside of the H.A.M. base. {{Chat option|4I'm looking for Jimmy the Chisel.|3And I suppose you need me to do you a favour?|2Ok, Jimmy has to be worth more than a few scrawny chickens!}}
*Talk to [[Fred the Farmer]] NE of the H.A.M. base at the [[Sheep Shearer]] quest start point. {{Chat option|3I need to talk to you about Jimmy.}} (4 if you haven't done Sheep Shearer)
*''Prepare a [[bowl of hot water]] and take a pot in the [[Lumbridge Castle]] kitchen if needed.''
*Talk to [[Seth Groats]] in the chicken farm east of [[River Lum]]. {{Chat option|2Oh, ok! I guess it's not that much further to Varrock!}} Gather 3 steel bars.
*Talk to [[Horvik]] at the armour shop in [[Varrock]]. Give him 3 steel bars. {{Chat option|3Hi, I need to talk to you about chicken cages!|2Ok, I guess one good turn deserves another.}}
*Talk to the [[Apothecary]] in Varrock south of the western bank. {{Chat option|2Talk about One Small Favour.|2I guess I can go to Barbarian Village.}}
*'''Travel tip:''' [[amulet of glory]] to [[Edgeville]], run south or use a [[skull sceptre]].
*Talk to [[Tassie Slipcast]] in the [[Barbarian Village]] at the pottery icon on the minimap. {{Chat option|1Ok, I'll deal with Hammerspike!}}
*Talk to [[Hammerspike Stoutbeard]] in the most western portion of the [[Dwarven Mines]] (SW of the [[Ice Mountain]] entrance). {{Chat option|3Oh, come on...do something nice for Tassie.|4Have you always been a gangster?|2Ok, another favour...I think I can manage that.}}
*'''Travel tip:''' If you have 10 [[Construction]] you can use [[Taverley teleport]]
*''Pick up the [[cup of tea]] from the house north of [[Sanfew]], then drink the tea to obtain an [[empty cup]], if you haven't got one already.''
*Talk to [[Sanfew]] on the top floor of the [[Taverley]] herblore shop about initiates. {{Chat option|3Are you taking any new initiates?|2Do you accept dwarves?|3A dwarf I know wants to become an initiate.|1Yep, it's a deal.}}
*Add your bowl of hot water to a teacup. Add a harralander, 2 guam leaves, and a marrentill.
*'''Travel tip:''' If you have 10 [[Construction]] you can use [[Taverley teleport]]
*Talk to [[Captain Bleemadge]] on top of [[White Wolf Mountain]] at the gnome glider icon on the minimap.{{Chat option|2I have a special tea here for you from Sanfew!|4Ok, I'll go and get you some T.R.A.S.H.}}
*Talk to [[Arhein]] on the Catherby docks south of the bank. {{Chat option|4I need to talk T.R.A.S.H to you.|1Yes, Ok, I'll do it!}}
*Talk to [[Phantuwti Fanstuwi Farsight]] in the building north of the Seers' chapel. {{Chat option|4Hi, can you give me a weather forecast?|5What can I do to help?|1Yes, Ok, I'll do it.}}
*'''Travel tip:''' teleport to the [[Fishing Guild]] using a [[skills necklace]].
*Enter the [[Goblin Cave]] south-east of the Fishing Guild. Go to the most NE room. Right-click and search the sculpture.
*'''Travel tip:''' [[Ardougne Teleport]]
*Talk to [[Wizard Cromperty]] in NE [[Ardougne]] at the transportation icon. {{Chat option|4I need to talk to you about a girl stuck in some rock!|2Oh! Ok, one more 'small favour' isn't going to kill me...I hope!}}
*'''Travel tip:''' [[Fishing Trawler]] [[Minigame Teleport]]
*Talk to [[Tindel Marchant]] on the [[Port Khazard]] south dock. {{Chat option|2Ask about iron oxide.|1Ok, I'll do it!}}
*'''Travel tip:''' [[fairy ring]] teleport ({{fairycode|AKS}}) or [[ring of dueling]] to [[Castle Wars]] and walk SE
*Bring your cut gems if you have them otherwise bring some gold in case you crush a gem in the upcoming step. 
*Talk to [[Rantz]] in the eastern Feldip Hills at the quest icon on the minimap. {{Chat option|2I need to talk to you about a mattress.|1Can you fill this mattress with feathers?|4Ok, I'll see what I can do.}}
*Talk to [[Gnormadium Avlafrim]] west of Rantz. {{Chat option|4Rantz said I should help you finish this project.|1Yes, I'll take a look at them.}} (at the gnome glider icon on the minimap)
*Search each landing light, cut the gem, and put the cut gem back. If you crush a gem, the gnome will sell you up to 2 new ones for 500 coins.
}}

===Completing the favours===
{{Checklist|
*Talk to Gnormadium Avlafrim. {{Chat option|4I've fixed all the lights!}}
*Talk to Rantz. {{Chat option|2Ok, I've helped that Gnome, he shouldn't bother you anymore.}}
*'''Travel Tip:''' Monastery Teleport via [[Ardougne cloak]] or use Port Khazard Teleport from [[Lunar Spellbook]]
*Talk to Tindel Marchant. {{Chat option|2I have the mattress.}}
*Talk to Wizard Cromperty in Ardougne. {{Chat option|4I have that iron oxide you asked for!}}
*''Take 5 pigeon cages (south of the north Ardougne bank) if needed, and get ready to fight [[Slagilith]].''
*Return to the fishing guild cave, stand in front of the sculpture and read the animate rock scroll.
*Kill the level 92 [[Slagilith]] (weak to Pickaxes and Crush attacks, immune to magic).
*Read the scroll again to free [[Petra]]. Make sure you '''finish the dialogue''' with her, or else you won't be able to make progress.
*Talk to [[Phantuwti Fanstuwi Farsight]] in Seers' Village. {{Chat option|4I've released Petra, she should have returned.|4I'll run through you if you don't give me that weather report.|2Why can't you get a clear picture?|2Which special Seers tools do you mean?|2You're talking in riddles, just give me a straight answer!|1What do you mean, 'special combination of items'?}}
*Climb to the roof of his house search the weather vane, use a hammer on it and search it again for 3 parts.
*Use each part on an anvil while holding a bronze, iron, and steel bar.
*Put each part back on the vane.
*Talk to Phantuwti Fanstuwi Farsight. {{Chat option|4I've fixed the weather vane!}}
*Talk to Arhein in Catherby. {{Chat option|4I have the weather report for you.}}
*Talk to Captain Bleemadge on White Wolf Mountain. {{Chat option|2Hey there, did you get your T.R.A.S.H?}}
*Talk to Sanfew in Taverley. {{Chat option|3Hi there, the Gnome Pilot has agreed to take you to see the ogres!}}
*Go to Hammerspike Stoutbeard in the Dwarven Mine.
*Kill his gang members, then talk to him again.
*Talk to Tassie Slipcast in Barbarian Village. She will give you clay. Spin it into a pot lid, then fire the pot lid in the pottery oven.
*Talk to the Apothecary with the pot lid and a pot. {{Chat option|2Talk about One Small Favour.}}
*Talk to Horvik in his [[Horvik's Smithy|shop]]. {{Chat option|3I have the tincture and breathing salts.}}
*Talk to Horvik '''again'''. {{Chat option|3I have the five pigeon cages you asked for!}}
*Talk to Seth Groats at the [[Lumbridge]] chicken farm.
*Talk to Johanhus in the HAM camp. {{Chat option|4You're in luck, I managed to swing that chicken deal for you.}}
*Talk to Aggie in Draynor. {{Chat option|2Good news! Jimmy has been released!}}
*Talk to Brian in Port Sarim. {{Chat option|3I've returned with good news.}}
*Talk to a Jungle forester. {{Chat option|1Good news, I have your sharpened axe!}}
*Talk to Yanni, wait for the dialogue to finish. {{Chat option|2Here's the red mahogany you asked for.}}
}}
