Romeo & Juliet/Quick guide:
{{Quick Guide}}
{{Infobox Quest
|name = Romeo & Juliet
|number = 4
|image = [[File:Romeo & Juliet.png|300px]]
|members = No
|release = [[4 January]] [[2001]]
|update = Runescape beta is now online!
|series = None
|difficulty = Novice
|developer = Paul Gower
}}

==Details==
{{Quest details
|description = [[Romeo]] and [[Juliet]] are desperately in love, but Juliet's father doesn't approve. Help them to find a way to get married and live happily ever after.
|start = Speak to Romeo in [[Varrock]] square or Juliet west of [[Varrock]]
|difficulty = 1
|length = Short
|requirements = 
|items = One [[cadava berries]].
}}

==Walkthrough==
{{Checklist|
*Talk to [[Romeo]] in or near [[Varrock]] square.{{Mainonly}} {{Chat option|3Perhaps I could help to find her for you?|1Yes, ok, I'll let her know.}}
*Talk to Juliet in the top floor of the house directly out of Varrock West gate.{{Chat option|3}}
*Give Juliet's letter to Romeo.{{Chat option|4}}
*Talk to [[Father Lawrence]] in the church east of Varrock Palace.
*Talk to the [[Apothecary]] behind the sword shop about the cadava potion. {{Chat option|2Talk about something else.|1Talk about Romeo & Juliet.}} ({{Chat option|2Talk about something else.|2Talk about Romeo & Juliet.}} If you have done [[Ratcatchers]])
*If you don't already have cadava berries, you can pick them directly west from the south-east Varrock mine. After that return to the Apothecary and talk to him.
*Give the potion to Juliet.
*Go back to Romeo and tell him to meet Juliet in the crypt.
}}

Quest complete!

