The Tourist Trap/Quick guide:
{{External|rs}}
{{Quick Guide}}
{{Infobox quest
|name = The Tourist Trap
|image = [[File:The Tourist Trap.png|300px]]
|number = 44
|members = Yes
|release = [[14 April]] [[2003]]
|update = New Throwing Weapons!
|series = Desert
|difficulty = Intermediate
|developer = Tytn H
}}
==Details==
{{Quest details
|start = [[Irena]], the woman crying on the [[Kharidian Desert]] side of the [[Shantay Pass]] south of [[Al Kharid]].
|difficulty = 2
|description = South of [[Al Kharid]] a new desert pass has opened up, leading to the dangers of the Kharid desert.
Don your desert garb and make sure your waterskin is full before heading off into the trackless dunes in search of desert adventure.
|length = Medium-Long (30 to 40 minutes if using [[energy potion]]s)
|requirements = *10 {{Skill clickpic|Fletching}} [[Fletching]]
*20 {{Skill clickpic|Smithing}} [[Smithing]]
*The ability to defeat a level 47 enemy.
|items = *2-3 full [[waterskin]]s
*Full [[Desert clothing]] ([[Desert shirt|Shirt]] (the one that looks like a robe top), [[Desert robe|Bottoms]], AND [[Desert boots|Boots]] required)(When trading clothes with the slave, you will need a desert robe, shirt, and boots to successfully trade for slave clothes). You WILL lose them
*1-3 [[Bronze bar]]s (Bought from Shantay, can be lost while experimenting)
*[[Hammer]]
*10-50 [[Feather]]s (must be white feathers)
*100 [[coins]]
*[[Shantay Pass]] or access to [[fairy rings]]
*All of the items can be bought from [[Shantay]] at the [[Shantay Pass]] (Bronze bars are often bought out by players training smithing, try hopping worlds if they are out of stock). Maybe, bring a few pieces of food while fighting the [[Mercenary Captain]].
'''Recommended:'''
*[[Knife]]
*[[Pickaxe]]
*[[Dramen staff]] and [[fairy ring]] teleports (such as [[Salve graveyard teleport]]s, a [[Necklace of passage]], [[Ardougne cloak 1]], etc) greatly reduces walking time.
*Weapon
|kills = [[Mercenary Captain]] ''(level 47)''
}}

==Walkthrough==
===Getting started===
{{Checklist|
*Begin the quest by talking to [[Irena]], located just south of [[Shantay Pass]] (fairy ring {{Fairycode|BIQ}}, then run northeast). {{Chat option|1What's the matter?|1When did she go into the desert?|2Is there a reward if I get her back?|1Okay Irena, calm down. I'll get your daughter back for you.|1Yes, I'll go on this quest!}}
}}
===Getting into the camp===
{{Checklist|
*Go to the [[Desert Mining Camp]] entrance (Directly south of Irena).
*Talk to the [[Mercenary Captain]]. {{Chat option|1Wow! A real captain!|2I'd love to work for a tough guy like you!|2Can't I do something for a strong Captain like you?|2Sorry Sir, I don't think I can do that.|1It's a funny captain who can't fight his own battles!}}
*He will attack you. Kill him and get the [[Metal key|key]] to the gate.
}}
<span style="color: red">'''Warning: '''</span>You will be arrested if you skip the dialogue and attack him.
{{Checklist|
*Unequip everything except your desert clothing and enter the gate.
}}
<span style="color: red">'''Warning:'''</span> You will be jailed if you equip armour or weapons or unequip your slave clothing while inside the camp!

===Getting into the mine===
{{Checklist|
*Talk to the Male slave on the east wall. (Not the south-east). {{Chat option|1I've just arrived.|2Oh yes, that sounds interesting.|1What's that then?|1I can try to undo them for you.|1It's funny you should say that...|1Yeah, okay, let's give it a go.|1}}
*Enter the mine to the north
*Follow the path until you reach a guarded cave entrance.
*Talk to one of the guards. {{Chat option|2I'd like to mine in a different area.|2Yes sir, you're quite right sir.|2Yes sir, we understand each other perfectly.}}
*Run back to the surface, unequip your slave robes, and leave the desert camp through the front gate, or return to fairy ring {{Fairycode|BIQ}}.
}}
===The plans===
{{Checklist|
*Talk to [[Al Shabim]] in the south tent in the [[Bedabin Camp]]. You will be given a [[Bedabin key]]. {{Chat option|1I am looking for a pineapple.|1Yes, I'm interested.}}
*Go back to the Desert Mining Camp '''(Make sure to put on slave outfit)'''
*Go up the ladder in the jail building and search the '''southwest bookcase''' on the western wall.
*In the same room, talk to [[Captain Siad]]. {{Chat option|1I wanted to have a chat?|5You seem to have a lot of books!|3So, you're interested in sailing?|1I could tell by the cut of your jib.}}
*Open the chest to obtain the [[technical plans]]. (Make sure you click continue, so the plans go to your inventory)
*Go back to the Bedabin Camp and show Al Shabim the plans. {{Chat option|1Yes, I'm very interested.|1Yes, I'm kind of curious.}}
*Use the anvil in the northern tent. Following the plans, create a [[prototype dart]]. 
**Use a bronze bar to create a [[prototype dart tip]].
**Use 10 feathers on the tip to create the dart.
*Take the dart to Al Shabim, who will in return give you the [[Tenti pineapple]].
}}
===Finding Ana===
{{Checklist|
*Equip your Slave outfit and head back to the guards in the mine with your pineapple and give it to one of them.
*Go through the cave entrance and head east until you're beside the mine cart.
*Search the nearby barrels to get a barrel. {{Chat option|1Yeah, cool!}}
*Get into the mine cart by searching it. {{Chat option|1Yes, of course.}}
}}
<span style="color: red">'''Warning:'''</span> Do not talk to Ana, she will alert the guards.
{{Checklist|
*Go down the west-northwest path and use a barrel on [[Ana]] (blonde hair in the northeast area).
}}
===Saving Ana===
{{Checklist|
*Head back to the mine cart. Put Ana in the mine cart, then take the cart yourself. {{Chat option|1Yes, of course.}}
*'''Search''' nearby barrels to find Ana.
*Put Ana on the winch bucket (northwest area of room).
*Don't raise the guard's suspicions when he offers help. {{Chat option|1Yes please.|1I said you were very gregarious!}}
}}
<span style="color: red">'''Warning:'''</span> Do not remove clothes to go to jail. If you do, you will have to mine 15 rocks to get out.
{{Checklist|
*Head back to the surface.
*Operate the winch (southwest in the camp), then search the barrel west of the winch to find Ana.
*Put Ana on the wooden cart at the centre of the Camp.
*Talk to the [[mine cart driver]]. {{Chat option|2Nice cart.|2One wagon wheel says to the other, 'I'll see you around'.|1'One good turn deserves another.'|3Fired... no, shot perhaps!|3In for a penny in for a pound.|3Well, you see, it's like this...|1Prison riot in ten minutes, get your cart out of here!|2You can't leave me here, I'll get killed!}}
*Get on the cart by searching it. {{Chat option|1Yes, I'll get on.}}
}}
<span style="color: red">'''Warning: '''</span>Do not try to teleport with Ana in your inventory, the barrel will drop first.
{{Checklist|
*Head back to Irena for your reward.
}}
'''Quest complete!'''

==Reward==
[[File:The Tourist Trap reward scroll.png|centre]]

*{{Skill clickpic|Quest|2}} [[Quest points]]
*4,650 [[Experience]] in your choice of two skills (you may pick same skill twice): {{Skill clickpic|Agility}} [[Agility]], {{Skill clickpic|Fletching}} [[Fletching]], {{Skill clickpic|Smithing}} [[Smithing]], or {{Skill clickpic|Thieving}} [[Thieving]].
*The ability to smith [[dart]]s.
*The [[wrought iron key]] - allows access to a special door inside the [[Desert Mining Camp]], which has several higher tier ores inside, including [[mithril ore]] and [[adamantite ore]].
*Full [[slave robes]]

==Required for completing==

*[[Desert Treasure]]

{{The Tourist Trap}}

